## Library Management System Flowchart

This flowchart provides an overview of the main processes in the library management system:

```plaintext
Start
  ↓
Display Menu
  ↓
User Choice
  ├─> **Add Book**
  │   └─> Input Details
  │   └─> Update Book List
  │   └─> Return to Menu
  │
  ├─> **Search Books**
  │   └─> Input Prefix
  │   └─> Loop Through Books
  │   └─> Display Matching Books
  │   └─> Return to Menu
  │
  ├─> **Print Who Borrowed Books**
  │   └─> Loop Through Borrow Records
  │   └─> Display Borrow Records
  │   └─> Return to Menu
  │
  ├─> **Print Library by ID**
  │   └─> Sort Books by ID
  │   └─> Display Books by ID
  │   └─> Return to Menu
  │
  ├─> **Print Library by Name**
  │   └─> Sort Books by Name
  │   └─> Display Books by Name
  │   └─> Return to Menu
  │
  ├─> **Print Books by Categories**
  │   └─> Loop Through Books
  │   └─> Display Books by Categories
  │   └─> Return to Menu
  │
  ├─> **Add User**
  │   └─> Input User Details
  │   └─> Update User List
  │   └─> Return to Menu
  │
  ├─> **User Borrow Book**
  │   └─> Input User ID and Book Name
  │   └─> Check Book Availability
  │       ├─> Available?
  │       │   ├─> Yes
  │       │   │   └─> Update Borrow Records
  │       │   │   └─> Decrease Book Quantity
  │       │   │   └─> Display "Book Borrowed Successfully"
  │       │   │   └─> Return to Menu
  │       │   └─> No
  │       │       └─> Display "Book Not Available"
  │       │       └─> Return to Menu
  │
  ├─> **User Return Book**
  │   └─> Input User ID and Book Name
  │   └─> Check Borrow Record
  │       ├─> Found?
  │       │   ├─> Yes
  │       │   │   └─> Update Borrow Records
  │       │   │   └─> Increase Book Quantity
  │       │   │   └─> Display "Book Returned Successfully"
  │       │   │   └─> Return to Menu
  │       │   └─> No
  │       │       └─> Display "Book Not Found in Borrow Records"
  │       │       └─> Return to Menu
  │
  ├─> **Print Users**
  │   └─> Loop Through Users
  │   └─> Display Users List
  │   └─> Return to Menu
  │
  └─> **Exit**
      ↓
     End


